observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive 

(a) create the Inventory Team to 

(i) undertake complete physical count of all property, plant and equipment and the inventories of the municipality and prepare the corresponding Report of the Physical Count of PPE and Inventories and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor within the prescribed period; 

(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant to maintain Supplies Ledger Cards and PPE Ledger Cards;

(c) direct the General Services Officer to maintain stock cards and property cards for supplies and PPE, respectively; and 


(d) require the General Services Officer and Municipal Accountant to reconcile their property records after the conduct of physical count to establish correctness of balances of PPE and Inventories accounts.

We recommended that the Municipal Development Council headed by the Local Chief Executive instruct the 

(a) Bids and Awards Committee to issue Notice of award (NOA) and ensure posting thereof to GPPB online portal for emergency procurement; 

(b) the Municipal Budget Officer to refrain from charging expenditures which are not aligned with the fund’s intended purpose; 

(c) Municipal Development Council to meticulously and judiciously plan the annual investment program and ensure that the PPAs implemented under the 20% Development Fund are geared towards the realization of the Municipality’s development targets and the attainment of the ultimate objective of improved quality of life for its constituents; and 

(d) Municipal Accountant to comply with the accounting and reporting guidelines on the receipt and utilization of 20% Development Fund to present fairly the expense and inventory accounts in the Financial Statements pursuant to COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 and COA Circular No. 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct the 

(a) Municipal Accountant, Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer (MDRRMO) and BAC Chairman to submit the required documents immediately to the Office of the Auditor for proper/further evaluation of the transactions pursuant to Section 4(6) of Presidential Decree No. 1445 and in compliance with the required reportorial requirements of GPPB Circular 2020-001; 

(b) Municipal Accountant to (i) comply with the accounting and reporting guidelines on the receipt and utilization of LDRRMF to present fairly the expense and inventory accounts in the Financial Statements pursuant to COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 and COA Circular No. 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015; 

(ii) ensure that all the disbursements are supported with complete required documents before making the payment; and 

(iii) ensure that all  the supporting documents are properly signed and the necessary information in various forms are properly and completely filled-up;  and

(c) designated MDRRMO to provide the Audit Team the copy of Projects/Programs/Activities of the allocation amounting to 3,150,000.00 to be used in validating the eligibility of the expenditures made out of the said allocation.
